<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="109" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1368,1899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1440,1466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized, wing length 5.5‒6.0mm (n=2). 
<emphasis box="[845,912,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Male:</emphasis>
Arista short-pubescent, longest branches 1.5‒2 times greatest width of arista. Head suffused with dark brown pruinosity on vertex, frons and parafacial plates. Frons at narrowest point about same width as ocellar tubercle. Entire mesonotum and dorsal abdomen also brownish black pruinose; paired trapezoid dark marks on the abdomen still visible in oblique views as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Baez, M." pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="619 - 670" refId="ref17198" refString="Baez, M. (1981) Dipteros de Canarias VIII: Tribus Limnophorini y Coenosiini (Dipt., Muscidae). Anuario de Estudios Canaricos, 27, 619 - 670." type="journal article" year="1981">Báez (1981</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 1, fig. 7). Also wing and calypteres smoky dark brown, contrasting with yellow halter. Dorsocentral setae 4 behind the suture; presutural acrostichal area with setulae only, arranged in two close-set rows. Mid femur with 3 
<emphasis box="[151,177,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">pv</emphasis>
setae on basal third; mid tibia with 2 
<emphasis box="[595,609,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">p</emphasis>
setae inserted above and one below middle. Hind femur with 5‒7 
<emphasis box="[1347,1373,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">av</emphasis>
setae on distal two-thirds and 3‒4 
<emphasis box="[477,503,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">pv</emphasis>
setae on basal third. Sternite I bare. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1241,1692,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[206,1371,207,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[183,1404,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Limnophora nitidithorax (Stein) (A‒C), L. obscurisquama Stein (D‒F). Males. Hypopygium, caudal (A, E) and lateral (B, F); sternite V (C, D). Separate scales for A‒C and D‒F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671818/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Figs 4D‒F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1260,1353,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Female:</emphasis>
Extensively dark-coloured as male, but dark marks on abdomen larger, partly confluent and shiny. Hind femur ventrally only with 3 distal 
<emphasis box="[353,379,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">av</emphasis>
setae. Ovipositor not examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1368,1899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1800,1826]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic Canarian species recorded only from Tenerife: La Orotava, 
<collectingRegion box="[1166,1290,1801,1827]" country="Philippines" name="Laguna" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">La Laguna</collectingRegion>
and Güimar (
<bibRefCitation author="Becker, T." box="[159,320,1836,1863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref17283" refString="Becker, T. (1908 a) Dipteren der Kanarischen Inseln. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 4, 1 - 180, 4 pls." type="journal article" year="1908">Becker 1908a</bibRefCitation>
), and Las Mercedes (
<bibRefCitation author="Baez, M." box="[565,692,1837,1863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="619 - 670" refId="ref17198" refString="Baez, M. (1981) Dipteros de Canarias VIII: Tribus Limnophorini y Coenosiini (Dipt., Muscidae). Anuario de Estudios Canaricos, 27, 619 - 670." type="journal article" year="1981">Báez 1981</bibRefCitation>
). A detailed review of the existing 
<typeStatus box="[1093,1141,1837,1863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">type</typeStatus>
material is given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pont, A. C." pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="31 - 166" refId="ref18496" refString="Pont, A. C. (2013) The Fanniidae and Muscidae (Diptera) described by Paul Stein (1852 - 1921). Zoosystematics and Evolution, 89, 31 - 166. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / zoos. 201300004" type="journal article" year="2013">Pont (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
